Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And with that, the match is over!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.30,0:00:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What I just discarded was the 6th White Dragon !
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.30,0:00:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Head bump?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.67,0:00:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This White Dragon Hiroyuki discarded wasn't a White Dragon at all
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.90,0:00:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I declared Ron on
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.00,0:00:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,the missing tile that discard was destined to be
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.17,0:00:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If there isn't a 5 Sou(bamboo) in that Mahjong case
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.80,0:00:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the point penalty KNOCKS YOU THE FUCK OUT!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.37,0:00:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,This swapped tile
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.97,0:00:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,was declared a 5 Sou by Akagi Shigeru when he decared Ron
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.12,0:00:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a reason that isn't such a wild guess
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.89,0:00:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You can read it off the discards
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.02,0:00:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a reading?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.02,0:00:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.02,0:00:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,In South round 1
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.79,0:00:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Harada's hand
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.46,0:00:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, yes
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.36,0:00:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,he declared Riichi on the 11th turn by discarding a 4 Sou (bamboo)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.52,0:00:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the end he didn't draw his tile.\NThe hand ended as a draw with Harada still in Tenpai
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.39,0:00:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,After the draw, his open hand showed he had 3 dora, a Mangan.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.19,0:01:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,A 7 Sou edge wait
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.72,0:01:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,When you saw that hand, did anything cross your mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.09,0:01:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Just for a moment I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.09,0:01:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,discarding the 4 Sou to declare Riichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.09,0:01:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that was very strange
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.09,0:01:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Keeping the 4 Sou...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.09,0:01:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and instead discarding the 8 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.09,0:01:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,then the 5 Sou wait would give an {\b1\i1}Ittsu{\b0\i0} with 3 Dora
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.59,0:01:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Mangan without declaring Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.59,0:01:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Clearly discarding the 5 Sou bothered him
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.12,0:01:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't it, though
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.19,0:01:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,throwing away a qualifying Yaku to instead declare Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.46,0:01:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,A most unlikely way to play
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.86,0:01:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason why Harada played the way he did,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.12,0:01:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is he decided the chance of the Ittsu wait was extremely slim
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.29,0:01:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.16,0:01:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps, in Soga's hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.16,0:01:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,There might have been a few 5 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.42,0:01:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally, he provided that information to Harada
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.09,0:01:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,he had that advantage
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.12,0:02:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I suppose that Harada just might also have known...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.02,0:02:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that there weren't four 5 Sou tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.96,0:02:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that in total, there were only 3...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.66,0:02:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Open the box
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.62,0:02:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Do it
