Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.36,0:03:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.07,0:04:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,As we expected, there's a fourth 5 tile inside
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.85,0:04:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, it's in there.\NThere's a 5 Sou (bamboo)!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.14,0:04:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And the last one...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.31,0:04:25.37,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,Okaay. Enough already
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.47,0:04:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a 5 Pin there
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.47,0:04:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi was also waiting on a 5 Pin
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.37,0:04:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That 5 Pin alone is enough. Case closed
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.67,0:04:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,B-but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.27,0:04:39.27,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,T-the FUCK?!?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.77,0:04:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The last one
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.77,0:04:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the sole remaining tile
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.87,0:04:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,HUNH?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.47,0:05:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He got it wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.21,0:05:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi got it wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.61,0:05:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,No
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.44,0:05:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,His reading was flawless
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.61,0:05:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Because Harada himself...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.61,0:05:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,wanted to give it up half way through
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.91,0:05:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That last tile
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.81,0:05:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,it really {\b1\i1}ought{\b0\i0} to have been a 5 sou
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.39,0:05:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,but in actuality it was 5 MAN
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.05,0:05:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Harada had ordered the 5 Sou and 5 Pin swapped with White Dragons
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.67,0:05:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but his underling mistook the order, not using a 5 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.07,0:05:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,instead swapping a 5 Man
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.47,0:05:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,A mistake like that, there's no way to predict it
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.61,0:05:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,B-but it doesn't matter!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.04,0:05:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi was in fact waiting on a 5 Pin as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.81,0:05:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The win is confirmed. Harada said it himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.74,0:06:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter. Akagi's win is complete!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.34,0:06:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Enough already!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.31,0:06:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Harada said it himself! Akagi has survived
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.07,0:06:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiroyuki...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.31,0:06:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all one
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.27,0:06:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What Harada says has nothing to do with it
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.61,0:06:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I declared a Ron on a 5 Sou\NAnd the missing tile wasn't a 5 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.14,0:06:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,To me, the result is all that matters
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.71,0:06:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need it. Winning like that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.84,0:06:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.01,0:06:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Harada
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.54,0:06:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a while since I've been here
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.07,0:07:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Was fun
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.84,0:07:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi is a most interesting man
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.56,0:07:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But no one is in Tenpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.46,0:07:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The contest isn't over yet
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.76,0:07:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The day of the final will be changed
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.06,0:07:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and the rules revised
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.66,0:07:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,both teams can suggest new ones
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.96,0:07:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Agreed
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.12,0:07:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,For all of us, after all this,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.12,0:07:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What in the world becomes of us?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.26,0:08:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,As I'm a human being I will perish
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.42,0:08:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and return to the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.89,0:08:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, after how many thousands of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.76,0:08:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,we're reborn as something else
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.46,0:08:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe as microbes spread throughout in the sea
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.36,0:08:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to be eaten by some faggy fish
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.99,0:08:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,or maybe as some whelp,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.22,0:08:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,or a bird
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.39,0:08:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't really care when I die
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.69,0:08:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,because life is reborn
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.56,0:08:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,but the one thing that bothers me
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.56,0:08:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,when I, as a human being, drop dead
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.82,0:08:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is this feeling of {\b1\i1}who I am{\b0\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.52,0:08:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that consciousness will vanish
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.29,0:08:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What really scares me
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.16,0:08:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,is becoming what I'm not
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.26,0:08:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And for that, I'm sorry
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.26,0:09:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.62,0:09:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I win,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.26,0:09:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,or should I fail,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.96,0:09:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's {\b1\i1}Akagi Shigeru{\b0\i0} who won...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.49,0:09:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,or lost
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.69,0:09:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever Harada does is of no consquence
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.46,0:09:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided that tile was a 5 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.62,0:09:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and the tile itself wasn't a 5 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.42,0:09:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the sole thing that's important
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.26,0:09:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.69,0:09:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's up to you now
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.79,0:10:08.26,Default - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(647.245,579.124)}Day of the East/West Final
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.36,0:10:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.49,0:10:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I ask you something?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.82,0:10:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If it had been you,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.16,0:10:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,would you have done the same as Akagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.59,0:10:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I remain
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.16,0:10:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,because if you don't remain, you can't win
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.22,0:10:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Remain
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.32,0:10:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm me. You're you.\NAkagi is Akagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.89,0:10:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,No one lives the same
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.66,0:10:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Here and now,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.66,0:10:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you and I have survived this far
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.36,0:10:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is everything
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.72,0:11:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's more
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.06,0:11:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I, above all else,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.12,0:11:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,concentrate wholeheartedly on victory
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.96,0:11:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and to that end I'll suggest a certain rule to the West team
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.16,0:11:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,a rule which can best play to your logical nature
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.59,0:11:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Ten, we've been waiting for you.\NThis way please
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.76,0:11:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,"Clear" Mahjong?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.19,0:11:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.76,0:11:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a Mahjong team variant that does without trading points
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.86,0:11:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a rule which awards victory to the team who clears 5 agreed upon Yaku
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.79,0:11:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The Yaku one must clear...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.46,0:11:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,are certain 2 Han Yaku
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.92,0:12:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Ittsu, Sansyoku, Chanta, Chtoitsu, SanAnKou
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.29,0:12:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Calling tiles is allowed
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.02,0:12:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you joking?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.46,0:12:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no reason why we have to agree to a foolish game like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.76,0:12:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.06,0:12:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine. We agree
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.19,0:12:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And your side?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.19,0:12:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The normal point system,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.12,0:12:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If a member goes bankrupt, that team loses.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.52,0:12:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's not just pure luck
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.82,0:12:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.82,0:12:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You're okay playing with both these rules together?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.79,0:12:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.66,0:12:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Proposing an idiotic rule like that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.66,0:12:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is proof enough they're cornered
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.86,0:13:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The Yaku which must be cleared...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.99,0:13:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,can largely be separated into two groups
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.59,0:13:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(648,124)}the first group, because it's a team game, offers protection against direct hits
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.11,0:13:10.25,Default - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(632,582.667)}East Round 1
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.52,0:13:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(634.667,129.333)}they are mobile, quick Yaku\Nfor which you can call tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.59,0:13:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,these are Ittsu, Sansyoku, and Chanta
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.96,0:13:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And on the other hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.16,0:13:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,there are laborious Yaku which you must construct on your own
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.86,0:13:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,namely, Chitoitsu and SanAnKou
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.02,0:13:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,specifically, of all five, SanAnKou is the biggest hurdle
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.59,0:13:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You might say it has the number one level of difficulty
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.36,0:14:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.82,0:14:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,A single suit hand？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.23,0:14:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.89,0:15:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The South team knows full well that SanAnKou is the key to Clear Mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.77,0:15:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So If I declare a closed Kan,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.65,0:15:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to the contrary, they ought to imagine I don't see the true worth a SanAnKou
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.75,0:15:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Soga's going for a Chinisou?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.66,0:15:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I declare a 2nd closed Kan
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.53,0:15:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,as you'd expect, they'll perceive I'm aiming for a SanAnKou
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.71,0:15:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Chii
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.16,0:16:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it!\NA confirmed SanAnKou
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.56,0:16:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only two 3 Sou tiles left
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.96,0:16:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,a terrible wait,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.72,0:16:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but if Hiroyuki has a 3 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.96,0:16:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and deals it into my hand,\Nmy SanAnKou is complete
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.92,0:16:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiroyuki,\NDo you have any 3 Sou?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.89,0:16:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have any
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.39,0:16:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What Sou tiles do you have?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.76,0:16:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,5 Sou, 7 Sou, 9 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.82,0:16:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, 1 Man
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.82,0:16:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Can he deal into my hand at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.96,0:16:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,As far as that's concerned
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.39,0:16:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,there's merely two tiles left on this 3/6 wait
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.06,0:16:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,just waiting for a win is almost impossible
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.29,0:17:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Without doubt he's got a Sou single suit hand
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.36,0:17:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone can clearly see this from his two exposed calls
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.09,0:17:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a danger he's on a 4 or 5 Sou double sided wait
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.32,0:17:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,HOWEVER
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.16,0:17:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the path I must take
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.29,0:17:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Chi
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.46,0:17:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,If I deal into his hand the risk of a foolish Haneman or Baiman hit is huge
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.29,0:17:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,HOWEVER
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.26,0:18:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Risk and Return are two sides of the same coin
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.26,0:18:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Into the jet black darkness of the game
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.69,0:18:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to stick your hand into the terrifying deeps
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.96,0:18:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It... passed
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.44,0:18:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, all Hiroyuki must do is deal in with his 5 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.06,0:18:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Judging merely by that Red Dragon
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.76,0:18:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,he ought not be discarding dora which are likely to complete Soga's Chinisou
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.42,0:18:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He's in tenpai for a huge hand
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.66,0:19:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,A SanAnKou?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.86,0:19:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If I leave it be for one turn
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.62,0:19:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and the kid deals into it, it's over
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.72,0:19:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,One moment now
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.39,0:19:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.92,0:19:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.31,0:20:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,When Harada flipped those two Dora indicators
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.61,0:20:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Swapping in tiles from his hand, he gave Ten's hand two Dora
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.59,0:20:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,With his Red Dragon Kan, it's a SanBaiMan hand
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.97,0:20:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,As the point value is so high, no one can deal into it
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.87,0:20:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We survived
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.34,0:20:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If the kid were to deal into that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.34,0:20:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,he'd only have 1000 points left
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.34,0:20:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,pretty much an act of suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.04,0:20:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and thus Ten's SanAnKou is no more
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.94,0:20:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Afterwards Soga will collect a 4 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.57,0:20:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,or I'll complete my hand and knock you out
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.07,0:21:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,no problem
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.25,0:21:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, kid. I took this hand last turn
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.13,0:21:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that's crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.57,0:21:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, Ten won't even accept that direct hit
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.20,0:21:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the way it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.67,0:22:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if that's your gut feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.07,0:22:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,it's okay then
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.07,0:22:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.90,0:22:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.47,0:22:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,24,000 points
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.15,0:22:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and SanAnKou has been cleared
